open scoped BigOperators
records.ground_truth:

  p.degree = @card (rootSet p ℂ) (rootSetFintype p ℂ) ↔
  Disjoint
  (@card (rootSet (derivative p) ℂ) (rootSetFintype (derivative p) ℂ))
  (@card (rootSet p ℂ) (rootSetFintype p ℂ)) :=

records.nl_statement: Suppose $k \geq 3, x, y \in \mathbb{R}^k, |x - y| = d > 0$, and $r > 0$. Prove that if $2r > d$, there are infinitely many $z \in \mathbb{R}^k$ such that $|z-x|=|z-y|=r$.

import Mathlib

open Topology Filter Real Complex TopologicalSpace Finset
open scoped BigOperators

theorem exercise_1_16a
  (n : ℕ)
  (d r : ℝ)
  (x y z : EuclideanSpace ℝ (Fin n)) -- R^n
  (h₁ : n ≥ 3)
  (h₂ : ‖x - y‖ = d)
  (h₃ : d > 0)
  (h₄ : r > 0)
  (h₅ : 2 * r > d)
  : Set.Infinite {z : EuclideanSpace ℝ (Fin n) | ‖z - x‖ = r ∧ ‖z - y‖ = r} :=

records.nl_statement: Show that if $X$ has a countable dense subset, every collection of disjoint open sets in $X$ is countable.
records.lean_header:
import Mathlib

open Filter Set TopologicalSpace
open scoped Topology
records.ground_truth:
theorem exercise_30_13 {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
  (h : ∃ (s : Set X), Countable s ∧ Dense s) (U : Set (Set X))
  (hU : ∀ (x y : Set X), x ∈ U → y ∈ U → x ≠ y → x ∩ y = ∅)
  (hUopen : ∀ (u : Set X), u ∈ U → IsOpen u) :
  Countable U :=
